verbose_text: Hydroxyproline levels (mug/mg ww) of scar tissue in groups which were applied with quercetin were significantly higher than groups which were not applied with quercetin (2.0 +/-0.2, 3.6 +/-0.3, 7.8 +/-0.8, 8.1 +/-0.6 for groups C3, DMSO3, Q3/20, Q3/100 respectively and 3.9 +/-0.5, 4.3 +/-0.5, 9.8 +/-0.8, 7.5 +/-0.7 for groups C7, DMSO7, Q7/20, Q7/100 respectively).
